OL,3,CGuernsey charities call for exemption
OL,4,Cfrom goods and service tax
OL,6,F"We do offer free meals to people who
OL,7,Fhave been supported by Grant Aid, but
OL,8,Fthe value of their money will be
OL,9,Freduced as well."
OL,11,FPlans submitted by the States of
OL,12,FGuernsey in 2023 suggest that
OL,13,Fcharities would not be exempt from
OL,14,FGST, meaning their donated goods and
OL,15,Fanything they purchase would see a 5%
OL,16,Fprice rise.
OL,18,FFor charities like Les Bourgs Hospice,
OL,19,Fthe only hospice on the island, GST
OL,20,Fcould lose them two full-time nurses.
