OL,3,CGuernsey charities call for exemption
OL,4,Cfrom goods and service tax
OL,6,F"Things are now beginning to get
OL,7,Fbetter, but what the Association is
OL,8,Flooking for is a restatement of that
OL,9,Fpartnership, whereby government
OL,10,Frespects that charities have frontline
OL,11,Fexperience and can deliver services
OL,12,Fmore effectively that they may be able
OL,13,Fto."
OL,15,FHe adds that the Association does not
OL,16,Fbelieve funding charities more would
OL,17,Fimpact revenue for other government
OL,18,Fservices.
