OL,3,CGuernsey charities call for exemption
OL,4,Cfrom goods and service tax
OL,6,FGordon Steele is the Chair of the
OL,7,FPollinator Project, which aims to
OL,8,Fprotect Guernsey's natural environment
OL,9,Fand presents special assemblies in the
OL,10,FBailiwick's schools on the role of
OL,11,Fpollinators.
OL,13,FThe charity receives funding from
OL,14,Fcorporate sponsors and occasional
OL,15,Fgrants through the Nature Commission
OL,16,Fbut has no direct financial support
OL,17,Ffrom the States.
OL,19,FGordon explains: "Funding is hard
OL,20,Fwork; it always has been and always
OL,21,Fwill be.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/9
